Description: Education-based youth eSports Club (ages 9-15) with games, activities, competitions, currency & prizes that will disrupt the tutoring market
Full Description: After graduating with high-tech degrees, followed by a Wharton MBA, the founder pursued a career in Aerospace working in Europe, Canada and the US with partners in Russia, Japan, Indonesia and multiple other countries. The founder's company, SAS Games, has developed the successful series of TiViTz math/strategy games and tournaments that have already motivated hundreds of thousands of students to master their math skills. TiViTz was recently named a Microsoft Education Partner of the Year and has won multiple awards from Dr. Toy to Creative Child to National Parenting to Parents' Choice. To reach millions more kids, SAS Games has spun off a new venture called TiViTz eSports to develop an online youth eSports club with games, competitions, activities, avatars, currency and prizes to address the lack of math skills in our youth and to offer a less expensive alternative to math tutoring. Due to the shift of kids' "heroes" from traditional sports teams to eSports players, TiViTz eSports has partnered with Team SoloMid (one of the most successful eSports teams in the world) for eSports-related prizes and for membership promotions of the TiViTz Dollar Math Club...where kids (ages 9-15) will compete in eSports-style TiViTz competitions (PvP, Battle Royale, Team Leagues). TiViTz eSports is currently in partnership discussions with several other eSports teams, including those in the NBA 2K, Rocket League and League of Legends. Unfortunately, most parents cannot afford the $40+ per hour for a math tutor. But fortunately, they can afford a $1 per week membership for a youth-driven TiViTz Dollar Math Club. By taking the approach of "kids helping kids speak math", TiViTz eSports will help address the looming STEM crisis...3M US STEM jobs unfilled by 2020 and 420M unfilled globally by 2030.  Bottom line: TiViTz eSports will harness the power of eSports to motivate kids to “speak math,” so they can pursue STEM careers, fill our Information Age jobs and shape the future...how many jobs can you think of that don’t involve ANY math?

Lost pledges go to successful challengers so you can make money sticking to your goals. Commit Club can be used alone or in a team as a training and development tool. Team mode uses a subscription model, and customers receive a dedicated community progress board, isolated pledge pool, and custom branding.

Full Description: Other Parents LIke Me (OPLM) is a robust online platform that supports parents who have children struggling with mental health issues, offering critical guidance and caring during a profoundly traumatic time.  At its core, OPLM is more than a website; in a very real sense, it’s like an extended family—one that features live support groups led by parents, expert speakers, a resource hub, directory and glossary. We currently have over 17 sessions each week. Our founders are passionate about this space, and their connection to OPLM is deeply personal.  They have endured life-altering challenges as parents whose children have suffered from various mental health concerns; in many cases, resources and community were unavailable or limited. These parents have enlisted a team of committed peer parents who run weekly support groups with one goal in mind: to help parents engage and move forward.  Other Parents Like Me, LLC (OPLM) lets parents know they are not alone. This online platform and virtual community is designed to create a safe space with the access and support parents need as they move from crisis to healing.  Membership includes: Daily Zoom Support Groups: Parent-led — currently offering multiple daily support groups, with early morning, identity-based, late night, and more Speakers & Expert Panels: Featuring parents and leading experts Member Accounts: Includes two unique profiles per account Parent Stories & Blog Posts: Insights into the journey of parents like you A Resource-rich Hub: Podcasts, articles, glossary, apps, books, videos, organizations  Support Directory: Professionals and organizations in the recovery/wellness space

The reason is that the majority of companies don't consider foreign candidates. But there is no way to know it in advance. To help job seekers multiple their chances to be hired abroad, we created a database of companies that accept workers from foreign countries, sponsor their visas, and provide support in obtaining work visas and permits. All the candidate needs is to pay for a subscription that grants full access to the list of 10 thousand companies and a hundred thousand open positions in 40 countries, including the USA and Canada, the UK, Sweden, Norway, and others. Each of them is hand-picked and verified by our team. We regularly update our records and remove closed positions. We also help subscribers increase their chances of getting a job by guiding them in how to build a resume and prepare for an interview. We return money in case the visa rejection. We launched the MVP five months ago, targeting job seekers from Eastern Europe, and met a great demand. We got about 60,000 visits and reached a 10% signeup to paid subscriber conversion rate. Our next stage is launching the service in India, where about 18 million people search for jobs abroad yearly, and most speak English. We're planning to launch the English version of the product this year. We also see a lot of potential in Bangladesh, the Philippines, Indonesia, Nigeria, Pakistan, Mexico, Brazil, and other markets. Years of the pandemic revealed the acute need for foreign human resources in developed economies. Many industries suffer from a shortage of workers, and companies are happy to accept foreign employees. In the USA, for example, there were 10 million unfilled jobs in 2021, and only 8.4 million workers were looking for new opportunities. This not going to change for the better. The developed economies will need more and more workers from abroad, and the candidates from developing countries will continue to look for a better life there. We are a team of 6 professionals with experience in web development, database building, marketing, design and project management. We are seeking 450,000 euros for 10% of our company. The money will allow us to launch in India and get to other markets faster. Our goal is to become the number one source of information about jobs overseas.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Industry Groups: Information Technology, Other, Sales and Marketing
